        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 16 at 4:22PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 422 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 14
miles south of Augusta, or 35 miles west of Cascade, moving southeast
at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bean Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
